# Kconfig — Kernel Configuration for Guardian LSM
#
# CONCEPTS:
#   Kconfig is the kernel's configuration language. It defines:
#     - CONFIG_ options that appear in `make menuconfig`
#     - Dependencies between options (depends on)
#     - Help text shown to users
#
#   When you add your module to security/Kconfig (by inserting
#   `source "security/guardian/Kconfig"`) and to security/Makefile
#   (by adding `obj-$(CONFIG_SECURITY_GUARDIAN) += guardian/`),
#   your module becomes a first-class kernel feature.
#
#   tristate: can be built as =y (built-in), =m (module), or =n (disabled)
#   bool:     only =y or =n
#   default:  default value if not configured

config SECURITY_GUARDIAN
	tristate "Guardian LSM (educational security module)"
	depends on SECURITY
	select SECURITYFS
	default n
	help
	  This enables the Guardian Linux Security Module, a demonstration
	  LSM that audits file opens, blocks file creation in /tmp by
	  non-root processes, and audits privilege escalation.

	  This module is for educational purposes. For production systems,
	  consider SELinux, AppArmor, or SMACK.

	  If unsure, say N.
